    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - IC BUS - DESCRIPTION - MUD
        GUARDS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MUD GUARDS</title>
        <para>The mud guards behind the front wheel, mounted on the hood/fender or fender extension, minimize damage to
            the lower edge of the cab from stone, gravel, splash and mud (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900503">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900503" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900503.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. IC BUS Rear Mud Guard</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MUD GUARD MOUNTING BOLTS (3) 1/4-20 x 3/4" Long HXHD SS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. REAR MUD GUARD</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MUD GUARD REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. MOUNTING NUT 1/4-20 NYLOK SS AND SS FLAT WASHER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
